# **1\. Project Overview**

\- My project generates an NBA Player's Information and has the user guess which player is being referenced. The stats and player info are accessed through [Basketball Head API](https://rapidapi.com/kdb-sports-kdb-sports-default/api/basketball-head). The list of players that the user can guess includes 6 players on each of the 30 NBA teams (180 in all). The user is first presented with the team of the player and prompted to guess. If the user continues guessing wrong, more and more hints are presented to them, with most of the hints being the different stats of the player and the final hint being the player's first name. The user can also ask for 2 extra hints, the number of All Star appearances the player has and the number of NBA championships they have. However, these 2 extra hints are only available if the user wants them, not by default.

**2\. Code Breakdown**  
**API.java**  
getData(String endpoint)

- Accessing and connecting to the Basketball Head API through the API key and an HTTPUrlConnection

getPlayerTeam(String ID)

- Returns the player's current team from the list of all of their teams in the API  
- Extracting the last index of the teams array  
- Splits the last index to ONLY return the team name and not the years played

getNumAllStars(String ID)

- Returns the number of All Star Selections the player has had  
- Extracting the accolades array in the API and iterating through the accolades array with a for loop  
- Returning the number of All Star selections (if any) in the format "(number)x All Star"

getNumChampionships(String ID)

- Returns the number of NBA Championships the player has  
- Extracting the accolades array and iterating through the array with a for loop  
- Returning the number of championships won (or the year the championship was won if it was only one)

static {}

- Static constructor initializes all of the player IDs to be utilized in the game  
- Learned from: [Static Initialization](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2420389/static-initialization-blocks)   
- the player IDs are extracted with this formula:  
* first 5 letters of player's last name \+ first 2 letters of player's first name \+ 01 (if no duplicates)

getAllPlayerIDs()

- Returns the playerIDs ArrayList that was initialized in the static constructor

generateRandomNum()

- Returning a randomNum with the formula \[(int)(Math.random() \* max \- min \+ 1\) \+ min\] to be able to pick a random index of the playerIDs ArrayList

parsePlayer(String jsonResponse)

- Parsing the JSON object into a player object with the player's name, id, and position

parsePlayerSeasonStats(String jsonResponse)

- Parsing the JSON object into a playerStats object with the player's points, rebounds, assists, turnovers, steals, blocks, field goals attempted, three pointers made, and free throws attempted per game

**NBAGame.java**  
main(String\[\] args)

- Entry point of the program  
- Picks a random index to choose from the playerIDs ArrayList  
- User is shown clues and is prompted to guess  
- Extra hints are also available at the user's disposal  
- After game ends, user is shown how many tries it took them and how many hints were utilized  
- If the user quits, they are shown how many players they guessed correctly throughout their run

**Player.java**

- Object class that includes the player's name, id, and position so the name and position can be displayed individually  
- Player's name is removed of accent marks with Normalizer, learned from: [Remove Accents From String](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/15190656/easy-way-to-remove-accents-from-a-unicode-string) 

**PlayerStats.java**

- Object class that includes all of the player's major stats so they can be displayed individually (points, rebounds, assists, steals, blocks, and three pointers made are the ones utilized in the game)
